00:54:35.240 --> 00:54:36.650
doing a lot more than the U.S.

00:54:36.650 --> 00:54:42.430
So the main forum for that is the U.N. Framework
Convention on Climate Change, international

00:54:42.430 --> 00:54:45.100
climate talks.

00:54:45.100 --> 00:54:51.071
In 1992 the whole world agreed to take the
actions necessary to avoid dangerous climate

00:54:51.071 --> 00:54:56.030
change, the U.S. Senate ratified that agreement,
also in there is the notion of common but

00:54:56.030 --> 00:55:01.119
differentiated responsibilities, that is the
rich developed countries of the world caused

00:55:01.119 --> 00:55:05.099
the problem, they will take the lead in solving
the problem.

00:55:05.099 --> 00:55:10.660
We signed that, we ratified it, the first
binding, concrete agreement to reduce emissions

00:55:10.660 --> 00:55:13.050
was in 1997 the Kyoto Protocol.

00:55:13.050 --> 00:55:17.890
When the Clinton Administration negotiated
that treaty they actually got a lot of concessions

00:55:17.890 --> 00:55:22.880
from the rest of the world in terms of making
the emissions reduction smaller and how those

00:55:22.880 --> 00:55:28.270
reductions would be achieved, but after signing
the agreement in Kyoto the U.S. Senate, it

00:55:28.270 --> 00:55:32.900
was never submitted to the U.S. Senate for
ratification because the U.S. Senate voted

00:55:32.900 --> 00:55:38.640
95 to 0 in a non-binding resolution that the
U.S. shouldn't do anything unless the rest

00:55:38.640 --> 00:55:41.380
of the world also took on binding targets.

00:55:41.380 --> 00:55:47.460
Kyoto Protocol has binding, mandatory reductions
from the developed countries of the world,

00:55:47.460 --> 00:55:52.349
while the developing countries would take
other actions as they try to reduce their

00:55:52.349 --> 00:55:55.470
emissions' intensity while they continue to
develop.

00:55:55.470 --> 00:56:01.730
I'm sorry to say that since '97 things have
continued to devolve, be happy to talk about

00:56:01.730 --> 00:56:10.220
it more after the talk if you'd like, but
it is just, the U.S. has been blocking progress

00:56:10.220 --> 00:56:15.020
at those talks and a lot of the rest of the
world is going on and doing more without the

00:56:15.020 --> 00:56:16.020
U.S.

00:56:16.020 --> 00:56:21.060
But we need to change things domestically
here and I think that's the number one thing

00:56:21.060 --> 00:56:24.420
that will jump start international progress.

